This is simply a collection of things mostly from other people that I used to upgrade an old Eldar Wraithlord to Seer status.

I repaired the elements from jimjimjimmyjim's wraithseer to make them more easily printable as they caused issues with my slicer.

It is all non-scaled and you need to fit it to your needs in your splicer (Cura worked pretty good for that purpose e.g. to inlay the rune into base and Shield)
- Spear is too large (lenght advis 130-140 mm)
- The Base is to high and to small (advise: diameter 65mm - height 8 mm)
- The Shield (longest length 25-30 mm)
- The gun is also too large (overall length should ideally be around 65mm --> scaling the canon trippel to a height of 25-30mm worked for me)
- rune and back is up to your liking.

I simply separted the work of kombatunit, and Named the .stl Files according to (http://eldar.arhicks.co.uk/miscellaneous/eldar_runes.php ) so you wont have to.

It was very practical to add individual runse on the printbed in the slicer (Cura).

I extended it by exactly Two Runes, one for "Wraithseer" and the other for the "avatar of Khaine".

If I ever feel the need to add other runes I will use this project to uploade them.

So I bought a Phantom Titan.
It's a great model.
I also remember the old Warlock Titans from years ago and wanted a more up to date 28mm scale version, so thought I could just make the bits I needed to convert a Phantom into a Warlock.

This is the Psychic Lance weapon.
It is designed to fit in the end of one of the lance weapons for the Eldar Phantom titan from ForgeWorld.
